Zodidi Mhlana JOHANNESBURG- A man in his 50’s died after the bakkie he was travelling in collided with another vehicle in Olievenhoutbosch, Centurion on Sunday morning. According to ER24, the man lost his life after paramedics had managed to free him from his vehicle. “When paramedics arrived on the scene shortly before 6, the fire brigade had extricated the man. He was found to be in a critical condition but despite the efforts of paramedics on scene, he succumbed to his injuries and was declared dead by ER24. The driver of the other vehicle sustained no injuries,” ER24 said. The cause of the accident is still unclear. In a separate accident, one man died and one was injured on Sunday morning after the vehicle they were travelling in rolled near Bosmansdam off ramp in Cape Town. Paramedics had to use jaws of life to remove the two from the vehicle. “Both men were found to be entrapped in the vehicle. The fire brigade and Metro EMS extricated the men using the jaws of life. SA paramedics and Reso medics also assisted on the scene. Upon further assessment, it was found that the one man sustained fatal injuries and he was declared dead on the scene by ER24. The other man sustained serious injuries. The exact circumstances surrounding the incident were not yet known to our paramedics but the police were on the scene for further investigations,” ER24 said. ER24 said that the injured person was taken to Groote Schuur hospital for medical treatment. @Mhlana
